@wjzav1971I’m NOT saying we should forbid diversity— not at all! I just think that when a movie features diverse characters for NO OTHER REASON THAN TO “APPEAR” AS IF THEY GIVE A CRAP ABOUT VARIED PEOPLE GROUPS—WHEN THEY REALLY DON’T— then I think THAT does a disservice to the diverse groups involved.

At the end of the day, what matter to me as a viewer is the acting ability of the actors, and that they aren’t treated as “props”.

Some of my favorite actors are Graham Greene, Andre Braugher, and Brad Douriff. Their race or sexual orientation doesn’t matter to me; they are simply excellent actors who played roles extremely well.

@DavidForsyth-k8y Oh my god, a fictional movie does not reflect reality! Call the police! Call the press! What is this madness!??
If there is one thing I know, its that every movie is otherwise 100% realistic! You totally can walk away from a big explosion without being hit by a shock wave or having your ear drums damaged! You can totally walk of being shot at or stabbed as long as it is not in the head or in the left side of the chest. Couples can know each other for only a few days and spent most of them bickering and arguing and it is totally gonna spawn a healthy relationship. Criminals totally get away when they were not read their Miranda Rights on arrest or when the arresting cop made a small error on the arrest form. One guy can totally beat up 50 dudes in a fight if he is just badass enough. Oh and highly trained soldiers will aways miss the good guys, even when they are out in the open without cover.
These are all things that Hollywood has taught me are 100% real so how dare they introduce something that does not reflect reality.
